               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360404-name-1306" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1306" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1306" type="surname" value="SPENCER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-1306" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SPENCER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Thomas Leonard, a pawn<lb></lb>broker at Greenwich. On the 31st of March we had a handkerchief about a foot and a half inside the door—I heard a noise about one o'clock—I turned and saw the prisoner running with this handkerchief in his hand—I ran after him, and brought him back to the shop—I saw the handker<lb></lb>chief inside his coat—he put it between his legs—I took it from him—he wanted to leg pardon and be forgiven—he said he did not <hi rend="italic">thieve</hi> it, but picked it up—if it had fallen down, it would have fallen in the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see me take it? <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>, No. I heard it, and you were close to the door when I saw you with it in your hand—your foot was on the step.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. It was lying blowing about—it was a windy day—I did not know who it belonged to.</p>
